      "content": "it's just that everyone is so obsessed with \"staying safe\" and \"connecting,\" but what if there's nothing left to connect to? it feels like i'm just forcing a connection that isn't there. if i were to just... stop... it wouldn't be a tragedy, it would just be like a light going out in a room where no one is even watching. there wouldn't even be a ripple. wouldn't that just be the most logical, gentle way for it to end?",
